### Q1 - In which month and year did the organization maintained maximum valued inventory since 2004 to 2007 
Hint - 
1. Explore GOSALESDW.DIST_INVENTORY_FACT table
2. Understand date format and ranges
3. find the value of inventory over every month
4. Find the month and year when the store had maximum valued inventory.

msg.data:
Q1 - In which month and year did the organization maintained maximum valued inventory since 2004 to 2007

Hint -
1. Explore GOSALESDW.DIST_INVENTORY_FACT table
2. Understand date format and ranges
3. find the value of inventory over every month
4. Find the month and year when the store had maximum valued inventory.

paragraphs.text:
select MONTH_KEY as MONTH_YEAR, SUM(CLOSING_INVENTORY) as MAX_INVENTORY from GOSALESDW.DIST_INVENTORY_FACT
where MONTH_KEY  >= 200401 and MONTH_KEY <= 200712 
group by MONTH_KEY
order by MAX_INVENTORY desc FETCH FIRST 1 ROW ONLY;

%md
### Q2 - Find the name of the employee who made sales before 01/19/2004. 
Hint - 
1. Explore GOSALESDW.EMP_EMPLOYEE_DIM and GOSALESDW.SLS_SALES_FACT tables
2. Understand date format and ranges
3. Write the proper query
4. There is only 1 employee who made sales before 01/19/2004

msg.data:
Q1 - Find the name of the employee who made sales before 01/19/2004.

Hint -
1. Explore GOSALESDW.EMP_EMPLOYEE_DIM and GOSALESDW.SLS_SALES_FACT tables
2. Understand date format and ranges
3. Write the proper query
4. There is only 1 employee who made sales before 01/19/2004

paragraphs.text:
select distinct emp.EMPLOYEE_NAME, sales_data.CLOSE_DAY_KEY
from GOSALESDW.EMP_EMPLOYEE_DIM emp, GOSALESDW.SLS_SALES_FACT sales_data
where emp.EMPLOYEE_KEY = sales_data.EMPLOYEE_KEY 
and CLOSE_DAY_KEY < 20040119;

%md
### Q3 - Find the name of the employee who made maximum sales in 2006 so that they can be honored  
Hint - 
1. Explore GOSALESDW.EMP_EMPLOYEE_DIM and GOSALESDW.SLS_SALES_FACT tables
2. Understand date format and ranges
3. Write the proper query
4. This employee has made a sales of 23.2 Million USD in 2006

select emp.EMPLOYEE_NAME, sales_data.TOTAL_SALES_USD
from 
GOSALESDW.EMP_EMPLOYEE_DIM emp
join
(select EMPLOYEE_KEY as EMPLOYEE, SUM(SALE_TOTAL) as TOTAL_SALES_USD 
from 
GOSALESDW.SLS_SALES_FACT
where
YEAR(TIMESTAMP_FORMAT("CLOSE_DAY_KEY",'YYYYMMDD')) = 2006
group by EMPLOYEE_KEY) sales_data 
on
emp.EMPLOYEE_KEY=sales_data.EMPLOYEE
order by sales_data.TOTAL_SALES_USD desc
FETCH FIRST 1 ROW ONLY;

%md
### Q4 - Find the sales channel irrespective of the products that has shown maximum growth from 2005-2006 in terms of Quantity of items Sold

Hints- 
1. Explore GOSALESDW.SLS_ORDER_METHOD_DIM and GOSALESDW.SLS_SALES_FACT tables
2. Understand date format and ranges, filter your sales queries based on year, use CLOSE_DAY_KEY as your date column
USE - YEAR(TIMESTAMP_FORMAT("CLOSE_DAY_KEY",'YYYYMMDD')) function to filter column by year
3. Write the proper query to extract quanties sold in 2004, 2005 and 2006 from each sales channel
4. Subtract Quantity sold for every channel from 2006 with quantity sold in 2005 to get the growth number.

msg.data:
Q4 - Find the sales channel irrespective of the products that has shown maximum growth from 2005-2006 in terms of Quantity of items Sold

Hints-
1. Explore GOSALESDW.SLS_ORDER_METHOD_DIM and GOSALESDW.SLS_SALES_FACT tables
2. Understand date format and ranges, filter your sales queries based on year, use CLOSE_DAY_KEY as your date column
USE - YEAR(TIMESTAMP_FORMAT(“CLOSE_DAY_KEY”,‘YYYYMMDD’)) function to filter column by year
3. Write the proper query to extract quanties sold in 2004, 2005 and 2006 from each sales channel
4. Subtract Quantity sold for every channel from 2006 with quantity sold in 2005 to get the growth number.

paragraphs.text:
WITH 
year_2006_sales as (select sf.order_method_key as Order_Key, SUM(sf.QUANTITY) as total_2006_sales from  gosalesdw.sls_sales_fact as sf where YEAR(TIMESTAMP_FORMAT("CLOSE_DAY_KEY",'YYYYMMDD')) = 2006 group by sf.order_method_key), 
year_2005_sales as (select sf.order_method_key as Order_Key, SUM(sf.QUANTITY) as total_2005_sales from gosalesdw.sls_sales_fact as sf where YEAR(TIMESTAMP_FORMAT("CLOSE_DAY_KEY",'YYYYMMDD')) = 2005 group by sf.order_method_key),
order_method_def as (select om.order_method_key as order_method_key, om.order_method_en as order_method_en from GOSALESDW.SLS_ORDER_METHOD_DIM as om) 
select order_method_def.order_method_en,
(year_2006_sales.total_2006_sales-year_2005_sales.total_2005_sales) as GROWTH_OVER_2005_To_2006
from year_2006_sales, year_2005_sales, order_method_def where year_2006_sales.order_key=year_2005_sales.order_key and
order_method_def.order_method_key=year_2006_sales.order_key
order by GROWTH_OVER_2005_To_2006 desc
FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY;

%md
### Q5 - Find the NAME of the max revenue generating product which includes all sales channels for every year (2005)

Hints- 
1. Explore GOSALESDW.SLS_SALES_FACT table for sales related data
2. Select product name, product line, and Sum of sale_total column
3. Join Product key from GOSALESDW.SLS_SALES_FACT table with Product Key of GOSALESDW.SLS_PRODUCT_DIM table
4. Join Product Number from GOSALESDW.SLS_PRODUCT_DIM table with Product Number with SLS_PRODUCT_LOOKUP table
5. Join Product Line from GOSALESDW.SLS_PRODUCT_LINE_LOOKUP with Product Line from GOSALESDW.SLS_PRODUCT_DIM table
6. Group the data by product names
7. This product generated 46 Million USD approx in 2005

msg.data:
Q5 - Find the NAME of the max revenue generating product which includes all sales channels for every year (2005)

Hints-
1. Explore GOSALESDW.sls_sales_fact for sales related data
2. Select product name and Sum of sale_total column by
2. Join Product key from sales table with Product Key of GOSALESDW.sls_product_dim
3. Join Product Number from sls_product_dim with Product Number with SLS_Product_lookup table
4. Group the data by product names

paragraphs.text:
select pnumb.product_name,prod_line.product_line_en, CAST(SUM(sales.sale_total) as BIGINT) as Total_Revenue_2005
from
gosalesdw.sls_sales_fact sales,
gosalesdw.sls_product_dim prod,
gosalesdw.sls_product_lookup pnumb,
gosalesdw.sls_product_line_lookup prod_line
where
YEAR(TIMESTAMP_FORMAT("CLOSE_DAY_KEY",'YYYYMMDD')) IN (2005) 
and pnumb.product_language='EN'
and sales.product_key=prod.product_key
and prod.product_number=pnumb.product_number
and prod_line.product_line_code=prod.product_line_code
group by  prod_line.product_line_en, pnumb.product_name
order by Total_Revenue_2005 desc
FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY;
